Statistical evidence suggests a genetic link to schizophrenia, with mutations in older men's sperm increasing risk.
In Sweden and Britain, research on 712,000 individuals born between 1973-1980 revealed a strong correlation between paternal age and schizophrenia.
Cannabis use among European teens is concerning, prompting a 10-million euro campaign in France to highlight its harmful effects.
Genetic research in Iceland uncovered a region on the 17th chromosome linked to common diseases.
Scientists aim to create a 3D model of the brain's circuitry to understand complex interactions at a molecular level, potentially revolutionizing neuroscience.
